## Requirements

Python 3

Flask

Docker

Docker Compose

## Installation

Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/Dorcas915/my-project.git
cd my-project


Create a .env file and add:

FLASK_ENV=developmhttp://localhost:5500ent
FLASK_APP=app.py


Build and start Docker container:

docker-compose up --build


Run migrations and seed file (if applicable):

flask db migrate
flask db upgrade


Navigate to:

http://localhost:5500


Test an endpoint using Postman:


Body (JSON):

{
    "temperature": 22,
    "humidity": 60,
    "soil_moisture": 45
}

